Catholic University traditional religion students explain use of sex herbs in marriages. They were part of the of students drawn from various tertiary institutions in the country who converged at the National University of Science and Technology (NUST) in Bulawayo under the banner of government iniatated Research and Intellectual Outputs-Science, Engineering and Technology (Rio-Set) to showcase innovative products that could be useful for the nation.Now in its third year, the 2016 edition of the Rio-Set expo which ran under the theme, Growing the Zimbabwean economy through innovations, was hosted in In partnership with TechnoMag s Tech@School initiative.The event was a huge success and showcased amazing work being done at several universities as shown in our video.Video by John Mokwetsi